        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 25 at 9:16PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 916 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Winston, or 7 miles
west of Douglasville, moving southeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, up to penny sized hail and frequent
cloud to ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Douglasville, City of South Fulton, Villa Rica, Chattahoochee
Hill, Lake Val-Do-Mar, Winston, Campbellton, Bill Arp, Chapel
Hill, Fairplay, and Hannah.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until midnight EDT for
north central and northwestern Georgia.</instruction>
